    "minides": "Nissan's flagship 7-seater SUV, reintroduced to India as a fully imported (CBU) model with a 1.5L VC-Turbo mild-hybrid petrol engine and CVT.",
    "description": "The fourth-generation Nissan X-Trail returned to India in August 2024 as a fully imported (CBU), single fully-loaded variant 7-seater SUV. It is powered exclusively by a 1.5-litre three-cylinder VC-Turbo (variable compression) mild-hybrid petrol engine producing 163 hp and 300 Nm, paired with a CVT automatic and front-wheel drive. The X-Trail focuses on comfort, refinement, and space over outright performance, featuring a panoramic sunroof, 8-inch touchscreen, 12.3-inch digital cluster, dual-zone climate control, and a 360-degree camera, while notably lacking ADAS, leather upholstery, powered front seats, and all-wheel drive compared to international variants."
  },
